{"name": "pyipasnhistory", "metadata": {"name": "pyipasnhistory", "version": "2.1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Information Technology", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "Intended Audience :: Telecommunications Industry", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "License :: Other/Proprietary License", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Internet", "Topic :: Security"], "home_page": "https://github.com/lookyloo/PyLookyloo", "license": "AGPL", "documentation_url": "https://pylookyloo.readthedocs.io/en/latest/", "dependencies": ["requests"], "summary": "Python client for IP ASN History", "upload_time": 1671791601}, "documentation": ["[![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/pyipasnhistory/badge/?version=latest)](https://pyipasnhistory.readthedocs.io/en/latest/)\n\n# PyIPASNHistory\n\nThis is the client API for [IP ASN History](https://github.com/D4-project/IPASN-History).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install pyipasnhistory\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Command line\n\nYou can use the `ipasnhistory` command to query the instance.\n\n```bash\nusage: ipasnhistory [-h] [--url URL] (--meta | --file FILE | --ip IP) [--source SOURCE] [--address_family ADDRESS_FAMILY] [--date DATE] [--first FIRST]\n                    [--last LAST]\n\nRun a query against IP ASN History\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --url URL             URL of the instance.\n  --meta                Get meta information.\n  --file FILE           Mass process queries from a file.\n  --ip IP               IP to lookup\n  --source SOURCE       Source to query (currently, only \"caida\" and \"ripe_rrc00\" are supported)\n  --address_family ADDRESS_FAMILY\n                        Can be either v4 or v6\n  --date DATE           Exact date to lookup. Fallback to most recent available.\n  --first FIRST         First date in the interval\n  --last LAST           Last date in the interval\n```\n\n### Library\n\nSee [API Reference](https://pyipasnhistory.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api_reference.html)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pyipasnhistory", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "pyipasnhistory.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pyipasnhistory.IPASNHistory", "xref": {"fqname": "pyipasnhistory.api.IPASNHistory", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pyipasnhistory.api", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pyipasnhistory.api.IPASNHistory", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pyipasnhistory.api.IPASNHistory.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "root_url", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyipasnhistory.api.IPASNHistory.is_up", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyipasnhistory.api.IPASNHistory.meta", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get meta information from the remote instance"]}, {"name": "pyipasnhistory.api.IPASNHistory.mass_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "list_to_cache", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Cac